    <div class="t2">
      <h2>Major pieces of Web</h2>
      <div class="t2_tp">
        <p>
          HTTP - Main Protocol of Internet<br>
          Server - A computer which is used to store composed documents of Web<br>
          Internet - The world largest computer net<br>
          Browser - A program run in your computer to display the files in Web<br>
        </P>
        <p id="p0_picture3">
          <img src="https://imgsa.baidu.com/forum/w%3D580/sign=6d08d03170310a55c424defc87444387/37e3432309f79052021c0dfc05f3d7ca7acbd5bc.jpg" alt="Here suppose to be a picture.">
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="t2">
      <h2>Summary</h2>
      <div class="p">
        <p>
          World Wide Web<br>
          World Wide Web is mainly composed by <span class="em"><em>HTML</em></span> documents.
          HTML is short for Hypertext Markup Language, which is the language <span class="em"><em>browser</em></span> used to parse web page.<br>
          The web components include <span class="em"><em>client</em></span> (your computer and browser),
          <span class="em"><em>Internet</em></span> and <span class="em"><em>servers</em></span>. <br>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="t2">
      <h2>Fundamental HTML Elements</h2>
      <div class="p">
        <p>
          <span class="em"><em>HTML Elements</em></span> are used to indicate how browsers display the contents in a web page.<br>
          Most HTML elements composed with <span class="em"><em>opening tag</em></span>, <span class="em"><em>closing tag</em></span> and the content between them.<br>
          &lt;<span class="tag"><span class="tag">b</span></span>&gt;text&lt;<span class="tag"><span class="tag">/b</span></span>&gt; bond <b>'text'</b><br>
          &lt;<span class="tag"><span class="tag">em</span></span>&gt;text&lt;<span class="tag"><span class="tag">/em</span></span>&gt; make <em>'text' italic</em><br>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="t2">
      <h2>Attributes of HTML</h2>
      <div class="p">
        <p>
          Some tags have additional parameters called <span class="em"><em>attribute</em></span>. Attributes provide additional information to browser.<br>
          For instance, link tag uses attribute <span class="em"><em>herf</em></span> to quote URL.<br>
        </p>
        <p>
          &lt;<span class="tag">a</span> <span class="attribute">href</span>=<span class="attr_value">"url"</span>&gt;link&lt;<span class="tag">/a</span>&gt; creates a hyperlink with the attribute herl = url, the name of the hyperlink is link.<br>
          &lt;<span class="tag">img</span> <span class="attribute">src</span>=<span class="attr_value">"url" </span><span class="attribute">alt</span>=<span class="attr_value">"text"</span>&gt; displays the image with address src = url (it can also be a local file of your computer),<br>
          if the image couldn't be shown, the attribute value of alt would be displayed.<br>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="t2">
      <h2>More HTML Elements</h2>
      <div class="p">
        <p>
          &lt;<span class="tag">p</span>&gt;text&lt;<span class="tag">/p</span>&gt; defines a paragraph. The contents of &lt;<span class="tag">p</span>&gt; are all in a box.<br>
          &lt;<span class="tag">br</span>&gt; is used to break line.<br>
          &lt;<span class="tag">div</span>&gt;content&lt;<span class="tag">/div</span>&gt; creates a block container element.<br>
          &lt;<span class="tag">span</span>&gt;content&lt;<span class="tag">/span</span>&gt; creates a inline container element.<br>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="t2">
      <h2>Structure of Document</h2>
      <div class="p">
        <p>
          &lt;<span class="tag">!DOCTYPE HTML</span>&gt;<br>
          &lt;<span class="tag">html</span>&gt;<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;<span class="tag">head</span>&gt;<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;<span class="tag">title</span>&gt;Title!&lt;<span class="tag">/title</span>&gt;<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;<span class="tag">/head</span>&gt;<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;<span class="tag">body</span>&gt;<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;<span class="tag">b</span>&gt;content&lt;<span class="tag">/b</span>&gt;<br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;<span class="tag">/body</span>&gt;<br>
          &lt;<span class="tag">/html</span>&gt;<br>
        </p>
        <div class="pic">
          <p id="p0_picture4">
